p: Our data indicate that Aedes aegypti and albopictus mosquito populations in New Orleans, Louisiana are not competent vectors for Zika virus given low levels of viremia ( Table 1). Only 1 Ae. aegypti was positive at 4 and 15 DPI while no Ae. albopictus were positive. None of the exposed mosquitoes had virus present in the saliva, indicating a low likelihood of successful establishment of Zika virus from low-level viremia and/or asymptomatic cases.
